THE Japanese Ambassador to Tanzania, Shinichi Gotoon Thursday launched a girls’ dormitory at Kimochi Secondary School in Moshi as the Embassy’s initiative to support the girl child attain better education.

This is part of the Grant Assistance for Grassroots Human Security Projects, under the Japanese Embassy that has enabled us to provide fully furnished accommodation to 64 students at a cost of 172,451,670/-.

The launch is part of a three-day press tour, which started on the 14th of this month, arranged by Japan International Cooperation Agency (JICA), where the Envoy visits various JICA projects in Dar es Salaam, Arusha, and Moshi, focused towards  the seventh Tokyo International Conference on African Development (TICAD 7).

Prime Minister Majaliwa and the Minister for Foreign Affairs and East African Cooperation Professor Palamagamba Kabudi are expected to attend the conference scheduled for Yokahama Japan from the 28th to the 30th of this month.